channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Supreme Court declines to hear reality star Josh Duggarâ€™s appeal of child pornography conviction
item.description: Former reality star Josh Duggar will remain in prison after the Supreme Court declined to hear his request for appeal to his 12-year prison sentence for child pornography.

item.title: Ric Grenell to Newsmax: Sanctuary Cities Undermine Democracy
item.description: Ric Grenell, who previously served as ambassador to Germany under President Donald Trump, told Newsmax on Monday that sanctuary cities are a nice name for a terrible idea.

item.title: Taiwan Attempting to Build Drone Army to Fend Off China - but Can They Do It?
Trump camp hits back after CNN host cuts feed, slams debate moderator's 'history of anti-Trump lies'
item.description: The Trump campaign said CNN has already proven the debate between former President Trump and President Biden will be unfair, citing Jake Tapper's "lies" about Trump.

item.title: Biden Fundraising Edge Fading as Trump's Climbs
item.description: President Joe Biden's reelection campaign's hopes of entering the remaining months of the 2024 campaign season with more cash appear to be fading, with financial reports showing a windfall of cash for former President Donald Trump rolling in, including the millions coming...

item.title: Prosecutors Recommend Criminal Charges Against Boeing
Illegal immigrant linked to Morin rape, murder by earlier assault of 9-year-old girl: cops
item.description: New details emerged in the murder case of Rachel Morin, a Maryland mother of five who was found dead last year near a hiking trail after being brutally beaten and raped.

item.title: Trump Lawyer Scharf to Newsmax: Prosecutions 'Never Supposed to Appear Political'
item.description: Will Scharf, former President Donald Trump's attorney, told Newsmax on Monday that Justice Department special counsel Jack Smith has repeatedly stressed the need to bring the cases against the former president to trial quickly.

item.title: Trump Campaign Opening Up the Map With New Offices in Minnesota, Virginia
Donald Trump has picked his running mate and they will be at Thursday's debate
item.description: Former President Trump says he knows who he will choose as his running mate, but says he has yet to reveal to anyone the name of that choice.

item.title: Speculation Melania Trump May Not Return to D.C. Full Time for 2nd Term
item.description: Melania Trump reportedly will avoid living or entertaining in Washington, D.C. as first lady if her husband, former President Donald Trump, wins the November election.

item.title: Desperate, Biden Admin Now Blatantly Lying About Its Friendliness to the Oil Industry
Liberal Illinois prosecutor Kim Foxx assaulted near her home, court records say
item.description: George Soros-backed Chicago-area prosecutor Kim Foxx was allegedly assaulted outside her home in Illinois on Saturday, according to court records.

item.title: NY, Colorado House Primaries Set for This Week
